  • Constructor Details

    • SwerveAutoBuilder

      public SwerveAutoBuilder(Supplier<edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose2d> poseSupplier, Consumer<edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose2d> resetPose, PIDConstants translationConstants, PIDConstants rotationConstants, Consumer<edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.ChassisSpeeds> outputChassisSpeeds, Map<String,edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command> eventMap, edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Subsystem... driveRequirements)
      Create an auto builder that will create command groups that will handle path following and triggering events.

      This auto builder will use PPSwerveControllerCommand to follow paths.

      Parameters:
      poseSupplier - A function that supplies the robot pose - use one of the odometry classes to provide this.
      resetPose - A consumer that accepts a Pose2d to reset robot odometry. This will typically be called once at the beginning of an auto.
      translationConstants - PID Constants for the controller that will correct for translation error
      rotationConstants - PID Constants for the controller that will correct for rotation error
      outputChassisSpeeds - A function that takes the output ChassisSpeeds from path following commands
      eventMap - Map of event marker names to the commands that should run when reaching that marker.
      driveRequirements - The subsystems that the path following commands should require. Usually just a Drive subsystem.

    • followPath

      public edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.CommandBase followPath(PathPlannerTrajectory trajectory)
      Description copied from class: BaseAutoBuilder
      Create a path following command for a given trajectory. This will not trigger any events while path following.

      Override this to create auto builders for your custom path following commands.

      Specified by:
      followPath in class BaseAutoBuilder
      Parameters:
      trajectory - The trajectory to follow
      Returns:
      A path following command for the given trajectory
